{
  "texts": [
    "It shows mean and standard deviation over 11 runs for each policy and replay buffer.",
    "128 SMILES strings are sampled in each episode, with a budget of 2000 episodes in total evident when using the diversity filter.",
    "A reason for this can be that there is a substantially larger number of molecular scaffolds generated when using a diversity filter which naturally leads to more topological scaffolds being the same.",
    "Molecules are generated using a model pre-trained on a data set derived from the ChEMBL database which will teach the agent to generate ChEMBL-like molecules.",
    "The DRD2 data set, which is used to create the scoring function, comprises data from both the ChEMBL and PubChem databases (Wang et al., 2017)."
  ]
}